      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): skip stale orphaned subagent sessions during restart recovery",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAfter a gateway restart, `recoverOrphanedSubagentSessions()` scans for interrupted subagent runs and attempts to resume them — but it did not check whether a run had exceeded the **existing** subagent run-liveness window. A subagent interrupted days ago could be resurrected on the next restart, replaying stale work and producing misleading late completions.\n\nThis PR adds a staleness check using the existing `isLiveUnendedSubagentRun()` from `subagent-run-liveness.ts` **before** attempting automatic recovery. Stale runs (exceeding `STALE_UNENDED_SUBAGENT_RUN_MS` = 2 hours, with `runTimeoutSeconds` extension respected) are finalized via `finalizeInterruptedSubagentRun()` instead of being resumed — so parent sessions receive clear failure notifications.\n\nThis approach:\n- Reuses the established liveness policy (no competing cutoff)\n- Respects `runTimeoutSeconds` extensions for long-running subagents\n- Covers both direct orphan recovery and restored-run paths (works on `runRecord`, not session `entry`)\n- Finalizes stale runs cleanly instead of silently skipping them\n\nFixes #90766\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/agents/subagent-orphan-recovery.ts`**: Import `isLiveUnendedSubagentRun` from `subagent-run-liveness.js`. Before attempting recovery, check if the run is still live. Stale runs are finalized via `finalizeInterruptedSubagentRun()` with a clear error message. Only 1 file, +30 lines.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Orphaned subagent runs with no liveness check can be resurrected long after they exceeded the run-liveness window, producing duplicate or contextless child-task work.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Node v22.22.0, Linux 4.19.112-2.el8.x86_64, commit 0272d13143. tsx v4.22.3 used to import the actual production module.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n1. Import the actual `isLiveUnendedSubagentRun` from `src/agents/subagent-run-liveness.js`\n2. Test 6 scenarios covering the liveness policy: recent run, stale run, long-timeout run, ended run, borderline 2h, just-over 2h\n3. Verify the policy correctly distinguishes live (recoverable) from stale (not recoverable) runs\n\n**Evidence after fix (terminal capture):**\n\n$ npx tsx -e 'const { isLiveUnendedSubagentRun } = await import(\"./src/agents/subagent-run-liveness.js\"); const now = Date.now(); const recent = isLiveUnendedSubagentRun({ startedAt: now - 30*60_000 }, now); console.log(\"Recent (30 min):\", recent ? \"LIVE\" : \"STALE\"); const stale = isLiveUnendedSubagentRun({ startedAt: now - 3*60*60_000 }, now); console.log(\"Stale (3 hours):\", stale ? \"LIVE\" : \"STALE\"); const longTimeout = isLiveUnendedSubagentRun({ startedAt: now - 3*60*60_000, runTimeoutSeconds: 4*60*60 }, now); console.log(\"Long timeout (4h to, 3h ago):\", longTimeout ? \"LIVE\" : \"STALE\"); const ended = isLiveUnendedSubagentRun({ startedAt: now - 5*60*60_000, endedAt: now - 60_000 }, now); console.log(\"Ended:\", ended ? \"LIVE\" : \"NOT LIVE\"); const borderline = isLiveUnendedSubagentRun({ startedAt: now - 2*60*60_000 }, now); console.log(\"2h borderline:\", borderline ? \"LIVE\" : \"STALE\"); const over = isLiveUnendedSubagentRun({ startedAt: now - 2*60*60_000 - 1 }, now); console.log(\"2h+1ms:\", over ? \"LIVE\" : \"STALE\");'\n\nRecent (30 min): LIVE\nStale (3 hours): STALE\nLong timeout (4h to, 3h ago): LIVE\nEnded: NOT LIVE\n2h borderline: LIVE\n2h+1ms: STALE\nexit code: 0\n\n**Observed result after fix:**\n- Recent run (30 min within 2h window) correctly classified as LIVE (would be recovered)\n- Stale run (3 hours, exceeds 2h window) correctly classified as STALE (would be finalized)\n- Long-timeout run (4h timeout, 3h ago) correctly classified as LIVE — respects `runTimeoutSeconds`\n- Already-ended run correctly classified as NOT LIVE (terminal, not unended)\n- Borderline at exactly 2h correctly LIVE\n- Just over 2h correctly STALE\n\n**What was not tested:**\n- Full gateway restart with real subagent sessions (requires live OpenClaw instance)\n- The `finalizeInterruptedSubagentRun()` notification path end-to-end\n- Interaction with the `scheduleOrphanRecovery()` retry loop",
        "branch": "fix/90766-orphan-recovery-stale-guard",
